Fred Itua, Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari has forwarded 43 names to the Senate for confirmation as federal ministers. Of the 43 names, about 12 were were returned, while a fresh 31 names were forwarded. Godswill Akpabio, Timipre Sylva, George Akume, Chris Ngige, Ogbonnaya Onu, among others were appointed. Meanwhile, the screening of newly-nominated ministerial nominees commences Wednesday, theÂ President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, has confirmed.